<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99961580466701></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99961580466701><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=?item=6260&mid=99961580466701>Certain death at that level</a> <a id=fs8 href=?item=6260&mid=99961580466701#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=26549><span id=Scholar>mcoolidge</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>155 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 4th 11:03 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.47]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not a chance. Here's why:<br><br>1.) Swarms. Everything in Befallen aggos on everyone, regardless of level. Level 35+ characters die routinely on the third floor, buried under waves of aggressive no-XP greenies that have way too many hitpoints.<br><br>2.) It's really hard to get 1-on-1 fights down there. maybe your 'chanter friend could help you. Do level 17 'chanters have AOE Mez?<br><br>3.) Escape. Getting down to the third floor is easy. Just jump down the well. Getting out is another matter entirely. You need to get through 2 locked doors - assuming here that you don't have the keys. Your 'chanter friend can just Gate out. You could get trapped (and killed) down there pretty easily.<br><br>When I went down there (I was looking for Pristine Leather but didn't find any), I was 35 (Ranger). We had a druid (to Evac us out), a cleric, and a bard along as well, similar levels. The cleric died (see Swarms, above). Then I died fighting the last of about a 7 or 8 MoB swarm. The druid and bard lived (luckily). While I was down there, a level 44 Enchantress who was camping the Primordial Ritualist bought the farm as well. We were able to get her a lvl49 Res, she gave me the next Servants Blade that dropped (she would'a given it anyway as it was totally useless to her).<br><br>Anyway - be careful. it's dangerous down there... But this is a really nice offhand for you Rangers out there. It's worth a little risk.<br><br>Arynduil Greyleaf<br>35th Ranger of Tunare<br>Norrathian Brotherhood, Erollsi Marr<br>&nbsp;<br><br>"In a crowded Universe, when the talking turns to noise, you almost start laughing"</td></tr>
